Describe a person's home that you liked but wouldn't want to live
- where it is
- what it is like
- why you visited it
- explain why you would not like to live there

I’d like to talk about my aunt’s house, which is a place I really enjoyed visiting, although I wouldn’t want to live there permanently. It is located in Củ Chi, a rural district on the outskirts of Ho Chi Minh City.

The last time I visited her house was about three years ago, during my summer holiday. At that time, I had a long break from school, so my parents and I decided to spend a few days there to relax and catch up with relatives.

What impressed me most about the house was its sheer size and peaceful surroundings. It is a large, well-designed house with a spacious layout. Outside, there is a huge garden where my aunt grows a wide variety of plants and flowers, which creates a very calming, nature-friendly atmosphere. Whenever I stood in the yard, I felt completely removed from the noise and stress of city life. Inside the house, it is bright and airy thanks to numerous large windows that allow plenty of natural light to come in. The interior is tastefully decorated, with wooden furniture that gives the place a warm and elegant feel, and all the rooms are equipped with modern amenities.

However, despite all these appealing features, I wouldn’t want to live there. The main reason is its remote location. It is quite far from the city center, which makes daily activities like shopping or commuting rather inconvenient. As someone who has grown up in an urban environment, I prefer having easy access to services and being surrounded by a lively neighborhood. Another reason is that the area can feel a bit eerie at night. Because it is so quiet and surrounded by nature, you can hear sounds like the wind, insects, and dogs barking, which I personally found unsettling. In fact, I remember struggling to sleep on my first night there.

In conclusion, although my aunt’s house is beautiful and ideal for those seeking peace and tranquility, it doesn’t suit my lifestyle or personal preferences.
